Responsibilities : 
Should have experience in developing Native and Cross Platform applications mobile applications using KONY Platform 9.0 is preferred. 
At least 5+ years of proven hands-on experience in design, development, and unit testing of Product and Services based mobile apps using KONY Platform KONY Visualizer, KONY Fabric, KONY Sync, KONY Messaging Service. 
Should have experience in managing a team, especially in the agile projects. 
In-depth knowledge on NFI/FFI; Interactive application development and memory management; Offline Sync process. 
Language requirements: JavaScript expert in writing/manipulating JavaScript codes/customization, Well versed on Core Java, HTML5, CSS, CSS3. 
Experience in Consuming webservices like Kony Middleware/Server like SOAP, JSON and XML. 
Good knowledge of protocols (e.g. HTTP, OAuth, REST, etc.) 
Certification on Kony will be added advantage. 
If candidate possess additional skills mentioned below it will be a added advantage carrying more weightage. 
Should have experience building enterprise level apps, and deployment to Kony server(s) 
Should have experience consuming web services through Kony middleware/server like SOAP, XML, JSON 
Should have experience with Kony pre-processors, post- processors, URL providers and connectors such as composite, looping 
Knowledge of repository tools such as Subversion, SVN & CVS 
Native app development experience will be an added advantage 
